            "description": "Two-loop H-graph (planar double box) with 2 massive matter (black-hole worldline) propagators of masses $m_1$ and $m_2$ and 5 massless graviton propagators, 4 massive external legs with two mass scales $m_1, m_2$ for 3PM binary black hole scattering. 40 master integrals. 6 square roots ($r_1,...,r_6$); the 6th root $r_6$ appears up to weight 4 only in a single MI computable in Feynman-parameter form. The remaining 39 MIs each involve up to weight 4 no more than 3 distinct roots from $\\{r_1,...,r_5\\}$, with piecewise (iterated-integral-by-iterated-integral) rationalization using different integration paths glued via Chen-Massey subtraction terms.",
